<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 2:12PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Marengo, southwestern Perry, south central Hale and west central
Dallas Counties through 245 PM CDT...
At 212 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Uniontown, moving south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Uniontown, Thomaston, Faunsdale, Dayton, Freddie Jones Field, Central
Mills, Consul, Perry County Correctional Center, Carleys, Safford and
Laneville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
